---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About - The National Angle"
  description="What The National Angle covers, how it approaches uncertainty, and what readers should expect."
>
  <article class="infoPage">
    <header class="infoHero">
      <div class="signalPills"><span>About</span><span>Independent</span><span>Evidence-led</span></div>
      <h1>Reporting the change before it becomes obvious</h1>
      <p class="pageDeck">The National Angle is an independent digital publication focused on the early indicators behind consequential changes in technology, business, politics, culture, and the world.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="infoGrid">
      <section>
        <p class="cardLabel">01</p>
        <h2>What we publish</h2>
        <p>We look for developments that are visible in primary records, credible reporting, public data, corporate activity, regulation, infrastructure, and institutional behavior. Our goal is to explain what has changed, what is known, what remains uncertain, and what readers should watch next.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <p class="cardLabel">02</p>
        <h2>How we choose an angle</h2>
        <p>We focus on observable developments that reveal a larger change or challenge the conventional account. A strong angle is grounded in evidence, clear about uncertainty, and useful without pretending to predict the future.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <p class="cardLabel">03</p>
        <h2>Our commitment</h2>
        <p>Articles should be clear about their evidence, link to useful sources when available, and be corrected when material facts change. The publication does not accept payment in exchange for favorable editorial coverage.</p>
      </section>
    </div>

    <div class="infoActions">
      <a class="btn primary" href="/latest">Read the latest</a>
      <a class="btn" href="/method">See our method</a>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
